Description: Shoulder sherd of East Greek (South Ionian) pottery oinochoe; light orange clay with much silver mica; exterior: dot-rosette on upper shoulder, broad band painted below; inscription cut on painted band.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis) (said to be)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.653)
